config_element.name: unifiGoogleMaxNumberOfPeriodicScans
config_element.description_user: Max number of periodic scans for Google scan.

config_element.name: unifiGoogleMaxRSSISampleSize
config_element.description_user: Max number of RSSI samples used for averaging RSSI in Google scan.

config_element.name: unifiGoogleMaxHotlistAPs
config_element.description_user: Max number of entries for hotlist APs in Google scan.

config_element.name: unifiGoogleMaxSignificantWifiChangeAPs
config_element.description_user: Max number of entries for significant WiFi change APs in Google scan.

config_element.name: unifiGoogleMaxBssidHistoryEntries
config_element.description_user: Max number of BSSID/RSSI that the device can hold in Google scan.

config_element.name: unifiBSSMaxIdlePeriodEnabled
config_element.description_user: If set STA will configure keep-alive with options specified in a received BSS max idle period IE

config_element.name: unifiMLMEConnectionTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Firmware waits for unifiMLMEConnectionTimeOut of no successful Tx/Rx (including beacon) to/from AP before it disconnects from AP.For STA case - Setting it to less than 3 seconds may result in frequent disconnection with the AP

config_element.name: unifiMLMEStationInactivityTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout for instigating ConnectonFailure procedures. Setting it to less than 3 seconds may result in frequent disconnection or roaming with the AP. Zero value disables the feature. Any value written lower than INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT becomes INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT.

config_element.name: unifiMLMECliInactivityTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout for instigating ConnectonFailure procedures. Zero value disables the feature. Any value written lower than INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT becomes INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEStationInitialKickTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout for sending the AP a NULL frame to kick off the EAPOL exchange.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEDataReferenceTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time allowed for the data in data references corresponding to MLME primitives to be made available to the firmware. The special value 0 specifies an infinite timeout.
config_element.description_internal: Note that the default has to be sufficient to allow for any MLME-SET.request used to set a different value! The value 65535 is reserved for future internal expansion (infinite timeout).

config_element.name: unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout
config_element.description_user: When UniFi enters power save mode it signals the new state by setting the power management bit in the frame control field of a NULL frame. It then remains active for the period since the previous unicast reception, or since the transmission of the NULL frame, whichever is later. This entry controls the maximum time during which UniFi will continue to listen for data. This allows any buffered data on a remote device to be cleared. Specifies an upper limit on the timeout. UniFi internally implements a proprietary algorithm to adapt the timeout depending upon the situation.This is used by firmware when current station VIF is only station VIF which can be scheduled

config_element.name: unifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout
config_element.description_user: When UniFi enters power save mode it signals the new state by setting the power management bit in the frame control field of a NULL frame. It then remains active for the period since the previous unicast reception, or since the transmission of the NULL frame, whichever is later. This entry controls the maximum time during which UniFi will continue to listen for data. This allows any buffered data on a remote device to be cleared. This is same as unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout but this value is considered only when we are doing multivif operations and other VIFs are waiting to be scheduled.Note that firmware automatically chooses one of unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout and unifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout depending upon the current situation.It is sensible to set unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout to be always more thanunifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout.

config_element.name: unifiDisableLegacyPowerSave
config_element.description_user: This affects Station VIF power save behaviour. Setting it to true will disable legacy power save (i.e. we wil use fast power save to retrieve data) Note that actually disables full power save mode (i.e sending trigger to retrieve frames which will be PS-POLL for legacy and QOS-NULL for UAPSD)

config_element.name: unifiDebugForceActive
config_element.description_user: Force station power save mode to be active (when scheduled). VIF scheduling, coex and other non-VIF specific reasons could still force power save on the VIF. Applies to all VIFs of type station (includes P2P client). is only provided for test purpose. Changes to the mib will only get applied after next host/mlme power management request.

config_element.name: unifiIdleModeLiteEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables Idle Mode Lite, if softAP is active, and there has been no activity for a time. Idle mode lite should not be active if host has sent a command to change key.

config_element.name: unifiIdleModeEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables Idle Mode, if single vif station is active, and there has been no activity for a time.

config_element.name: unifiMacrameDebugStats
config_element.description_user: MACRAME debug stats readout key. Use set to write a debug readout, then read the same key to get the actual readout.

config_element.name: unifiNANEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables Neighbour Aware Networking (NAN)

config_element.name: unifiNANBeaconCapabilities
config_element.description_user: The 16-bit field follows the coding of IEEE 802.11 Capability Information.

config_element.name: unifiLowPowerRxConfig
config_element.description_user: Enables low power radio RX for idle STA and AP VIFs respectively. Setting/clearing bit 0 enables/disabled LP RX for (all) STA/Cli VIFs. Setting/clearing bit 1 enables/disabled LP RX for AP/GO VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiStationActivityIdleTime
config_element.description_user: Time since last station activity when it can be considered to be idle. Only used in SoftAP mode when determining if all connected stations are idle (not active).

config_element.name: unifiApBeaconMaxDrift
config_element.description_user: The maximum drift in microseconds we will allow for each beacon sent when we're trying to move it to get a 50% duty cycle between GO and STA in multiple VIF scenario. We'll delay our TX beacon by a maximum of this value until we reach our target TBTT. We have 3 possible cases for this value: a) ap_beacon_max_drift = 0x0000 - Feature disabled b) ap_beacon_max_drift between 0x0001 and 0xFFFE - Each time we transmit the beacon we'll move it a little bit forward but never more than this. (Not implemented yet) c) ap_beacon_max_drift = 0xFFFF - Move the beacon to the desired position in one shot.

config_element.name: unifiMacBeaconTimeout
config_element.description_user: The maximum time in microseconds we want to stall TX data when expecting a beacon at EBRT time as a station.

config_element.name: unifiRSSIMaxAveragingPeriod
config_element.description_user: Limits the period over which the value of unifiRSSI is averaged. If no more than unifiRSSIMinReceivedFrames frames have been received in the period, then the value of unifiRSSI is reset to the value of the next measurement and the rolling average is restarted. This ensures that the value is timely (although possibly poorly averaged) when little data is being received.

config_element.name: unifiRSSIMinReceivedFrames
config_element.description_user: See the description of unifiRSSIMaxAveragingPeriod for how the combination of attributes is used.

config_element.name: unifiCSROnlyEIFSDuration
config_element.description_user: Specifies time that is used for EIFS. A value of 0 causes the build in value to be used.

config_element.name: unifiForceChannelBW
config_element.description_user: Test/debug Mib to force channel bandwidth to specified value. This can also be used to allow emulator/silicon back to back connection to communicate at bandwidth other than default (20 MHz) Setting it to 0 uses the default bandwidth as selected by firmware channel_bw_20_mhz = 20, channel_bw_40_mhz = 40, channel_bw_80_mhz = 80

config_element.name: unifiTestSetChannelBW
config_element.description_user: Test/debug Mib to set channel bandwidth to specified value.

config_element.name: unifiSwToHwQueueStats
config_element.description_user: The timing statistics of packets being queued between SW-HW

config_element.name: unifiHostToSwQueueStats
config_element.description_user: The timing statistics of packets being queued between HOST-SW

config_element.name: unifiQueueStatsEnable
config_element.description_user: Enables recording timing statistics of packets being queued between HOST-SW-HW

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsRate
config_element.description_user: The rate corresponding to the current table entry. The value is rounded to the nearest number of units where necessary. Most rates do not require rounding, but when short guard interval is in effect the rates are no longer multiples of the base unit. Note that there may be two occurrences of the value 130: the first corresponds to MCS index 7, and the second, if present, to MCS index 6 with short guard interval.
config_element.description_internal: Get the rate for rate statistics table entry index.

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsRxSuccessCount
config_element.description_user: The number of successful receptions of complete management and data frames at the rate indexed by unifiRateStatsIndex.This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsTxSuccessCount
config_element.description_user: The number of successful (acknowledged) unicast transmissions of complete data or management frames the rate indexed by unifiRateStatsIndex. This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiTxDataConfirm
config_element.description_user: Allows to request on a per access class basis that an MA_UNITDATA.confirm be generated after each packet transfer. The default value is applied for all ACs.

config_element.name: unifiTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The bit rate currently in use for transmissions of unicast data frames; On an infrastructure BSS, this is the data rate used in communicating with the associated access point, if there is none, an error is returned
config_element.description_internal: Request is made per-VIF. Rate is read from station records

config_element.name: unifiLastBssTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: Last BSS Tx DataRate. See unifiTxDataRate description.

config_element.name: unifiRxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The bit rate of the last received frame on this VIF.
config_element.description_internal: Request is made per-VIF and only support for STA VIF type.

config_element.name: unifiNoAckActivationCount
config_element.description_user: The number of frames that are discarded due to HW No-ack activated during test. This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.
config_element.description_internal: Number of discarded frames when HW No-ack is activated during test.

config_element.name: unifiRxFcsErrorCount
config_element.description_user: The number of received frames that are discarded due to bad FCS (CRC). This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.
config_element.description_internal: Number of discarded received frames due to bad FCS (CRC) as detected by the HW.

config_element.name: unifiReadReg
config_element.description_user: Read value from a register and return it.
config_element.description_internal: Register access function.

config_element.name: unifiReadHardwareCounter
config_element.description_user: Read a value from a hardware packet counter in a specific mac instance and return it.
config_element.description_internal: Hardware counter access function.

config_element.name: unifiRsnCapabilities
config_element.description_user: Encodes the RSN Capabilities field of IEEE 802.11 RSN Information Element.

config_element.name: unifiHwTxTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time in milliseconds for a frame to be queued in the hardware/DPIF.

config_element.name: unifiSwTxTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time in seconds for a frame to be queued in firmware, ready to be sent, but not yet actually pumped to hardware.

config_element.name: unifiSNR
config_element.description_user: Provides a running average of the Signal to Noise Ratio (SNR) for packets received by UniFi's radio.

config_element.name: unifiLastBssSNR
config_element.description_user: Last BSS SNR. See unifiSNR description.

config_element.name: unifiSNRExtraOffsetCCK
config_element.description_user: This offset is added to SNR values received at 802.11b data rates. This accounts for differences in the RF pathway between 802.11b and 802.11g demodulators. The offset applies to values of unifiSNR as well as SNR values in scan indications. Not used in 5GHz mode.

config_element.name: unifiScanMaxProbeTransmitLifetime
config_element.description_user: If non-zero, used during active scans as the maximum lifetime for probe requests. It is the elapsed time after the initial transmission at which further attempts to transmit the probe are terminated.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseNonAPLifetime
config_element.description_user: Lifetime of proberesponse frame in unit of ms for all vifs which are not an infrastructe AP.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseAPLifetime
config_element.description_user: Lifetime of proberesponse frame in unit of ms for infrastructure AP.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseMaxRetry
config_element.description_user: Number of retries of probe response frame.

config_element.name: unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold
config_element.description_user: If VIF has this many packets queued/transmitted/received in last unifiFastPowerSaveTransitionPeriod then firmware may decide to come out of aggressive power save mode. This is applicable to STA (CLI) and GO (VIF).Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB.Also see unifiExitPowerSavePeriod and unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod.

config_element.name: unifiExitPowerSavePeriod
config_element.description_user: Period in TUs over which firmware counts number of packet transmitted/queued/received to decide to come out of aggressive power save mode. This is applicable to STA (CLI) and GO (AP) VIF. Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB. Also see unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold and unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod

config_element.name: unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod
config_element.description_user: Defines how many unifiExitPowerSavePeriod firmware should wait in which VIF had received/transmitted/queued less than unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold packets - before entering aggressive power save mode (when not in aggressive power save mode) This is applicable to STA (CLI) and GO (AP) VIF. Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB. Also see unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold and unifiExitPowerSavePeriod.

config_element.name: unifiActiveTimeAfterMoreBit
config_element.description_user: After seeing the "more" bit set in a message from the AP, the STA will goto active mode for this duration of time. After this time, traffic information is evaluated to determine whether the STA should stay active or go to powersave. Setting this value to 0 means that the described functionality is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiForcedScheduleDuration
config_element.description_user: Defines the time to keep a VIF scheduled after an outgoing packet is queued, if the "Immediate_Response_Expected" bit is set in the Tx_Control associated with a frame transmission request. The firmware may choose to override this value based on internal logic.

config_element.name: unifiMAXVifScheduleDuration
config_element.description_user: Default time for which a non-scan VIF can be scheduled. Applies to multiVIF scenario. Internal firmware logic or BSS state (e.g. NOA) may cut short the schedule.

config_element.name: unifiVifLongIntervalTime
config_element.description_user: When the scheduler expects a VIF to schedule for time longer than this parameter (specified in TUs), then the VIF may come out of powersave. Only valid for STA VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiUartConfigure
config_element.description_user: UART configuration using the values of the other unifiUart* attributes. The value supplied for this attribute is ignored.

config_element.name: unifiUartPios
config_element.description_user: Specification of which PIOs should be connected to the UART. Currently defined values are: 1 - UART not used; all PIOs are available for other uses. 2 - Data transmit and receive connected to PIO[12] and PIO[14] respectively. No hardware handshaking lines. 3 - Data and handshaking lines connected to PIO[12:15].

config_element.name: unifiWatchdogTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time the background may be busy or locked out for. If this time is exceeded, UniFi will reset. If this key is set to 65535 then the watchdog will be disabled.

config_element.name: unifiLoggerEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable reporting of the following events for Android logging: - firmware connectivity events - fate of management frames sent by the host through the MLME SAP It can take the following values: - 0: reporting is disabled - 1: partial reporting is enabled. Beacons and EAPOL frames will not be reported - 2: full reporting is enabled. Beacons and EAPOL frames are included.

config_element.name: unifiLoggerMaxDelayedEvents
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of events to keep when host is suspended.

config_element.name: unifiMaPacketFateEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable reporting of the fate of the TX packets sent by the host

config_element.name: unifiForceShortSlotTime
config_element.description_user: If set to true, forces FW to use short slot times for all VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiRSSI
config_element.description_user: Running average of the Received Signal Strength Indication (RSSI) for packets received by UniFi's radio. The value should only be treated as an indication of the signal strength; it is not an accurate measurement. The result is only meaningful if the unifiRxExternalGain attribute is set to the correct calibration value. If UniFi is part of a BSS, only frames originating from devices in the BSS are reported (so far as this can be determined). The average is reset when UniFi joins or starts a BSS or is reset.
config_element.description_internal: Use the lack of a (default) value to signal to rame that the RSSI hasn't been calibrated, and thus calls to mibgetrssi() will return FALSE.

config_element.name: unifiLastBssRSSI
config_element.description_user: Last BSS RSSI. See unifiRSSI description.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconCu
config_element.description_user: Provides a channel utilization of peer, value 255=100% channel utilization.

config_element.name: unifiPeerBandwidth
config_element.description_user: The bandwidth used with peer station prior it disconnects

config_element.name: unifiCurrentPeerNss
config_element.description_user: The number of spatial streams used with peer station prior it disconnects

config_element.name: unifiPeerTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The tx rate that was used for transmissions prior disconnection;

config_element.name: unifiPeerRSSI
config_element.description_user: The recorded RSSI from peer station prior it disconnects

config_element.name: unifiTxSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter settings

config_element.name: unifiTxGainSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter gain settings

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerDetectorResponse
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter detector response settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxDetectorTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter detector temperature compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxDetectorFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter detector frequency compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxOpenLoopTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter open-loop temperature compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxOpenLoopFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter open-loop frequency compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxPaGainDpdTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter PA gain for DPD temperature compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxPaGainDpdFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter PA gain for DPD frequency compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxFtrimSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter frequency compensation settings

config_element.name: unifiTxGainStepSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter gain step settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxOfdmSelect
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter OFDM selection settings

config_element.name: unifiTxDigGain
config_element.description_user: Specify gain specific modulation power optimisation.

config_element.name: unifiChipTemperature
config_element.description_user: Read the chip temperature as seen by WLAN radio firmware.

config_element.name: UnifiBatteryVoltage
config_element.description_user: Battery voltage

config_element.name: unifiLoadDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a static DPD LUT to the FW
config_element.description_internal: For testing: Write DPD LUT entry

config_element.name: unifiOverrideDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a DPD LUT directly to the HW
config_element.description_internal: Used for Matlab characterisation by writing a previously calculated and (possibly) smoothed LUT to the HW. The primary need for this is because writing the LUT directly in Matlab is very slow and hence impractical for any characterisation work.

config_element.name: unifiDpdPredistortGains
config_element.description_user: DPD pre-distort gains. Takes a range of frequencies, where f_min <= f_channel < f_max. The format is [freq_min_msb, freq_min_lsb, freq_max_msb, freq_max_lsb, DPD policy bitmap, bandwidth_bitmap, power_trim_enable, OFDM0_gain, OFDM1_gain, CCK_gain, TR_gain, CCK PSAT gain, OFDM PSAT gain].

config_element.name: unifiDpdMasterSwitch
config_element.description_user: Enables Digital Pre-Distortion
config_element.description_internal: Bitmask of DPD features to enable for testing, requires d01_d01 or later.

config_element.name: unifiCCAMasterSwitch
config_element.description_user: Enables CCA
config_element.description_internal: Bitmask of CCA features to enable.

config_element.name: unifiBbBbaCcaCfg
config_element.description_user: Enables/disables CCA
config_element.description_internal:
Bitmask of CCA features to enable in PHY. Changes applied when radio is next switched on. To enable: mlme_set_req 5108 0 . 0 To disable: mlme_set_req 5108 255 . 0
Note in the example above, it disables the CCA STF and so will prevent packet sync.

config_element.name: unifiRxSyncCCACfg
config_element.description_user: Configures CCA per 20 MHz sub-band.
config_element.description_internal: Configure to take into account the CCA of each 20M subband for the primary channel.

config_element.name: unifiMacCCABusyTime
config_element.description_user: Counts the time CCA indicates busy
config_element.description_internal: This register counts the time CCA indicates busy (for pri20/sec20 and sec40), in units of 16 us.

config_element.name: unifiMacSecChanClearTime
config_element.description_user: Configures PIFS
config_element.description_internal: Secondary Channel must be free for this amount of time (50ns unit) before it is declared non-busy for starting a Txop. Related to PIFS.

config_element.name: unifiCCACSThresh
config_element.description_user: Configures CCA CS thresholds.
config_element.description_internal: Configures CCA CS (packet sync) thresholds. Indexed by siso/mimo.

config_element.name: unifiCoexDebugOverrideBt
config_element.description_user: Enables overriding of all BT activities by WLAN.
config_element.description_internal: When this MIB is set then no macrame blackouts are registered for any BT activities and also WLAN trumps all BT activities at the HW CDL arbitration level. This MIB should be enabled only for debugging purposes. This MIB will only have an effect when its either compiled into the FW image or is configured at WLAN boot via an hcf file.

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerTrimConfig
config_element.description_user: Configuration settings for the TX power trim. The format is [band, pcal_ofdm0_to_cck_mso, pcal_ofdm0_to_cck_lso, pcal_ofdm0_to_ofdm1_mso, pcal_ofdm0_to_ofdm1_lso, pcal_20_to_80_mso, pcal_20_to_80_lso, pcal_20_to_40_mso, pcal_20_to_40_lso, psat_v2i_gain, psat_mix_gain, psat_drv_gain, psat_pa_gain, psat_power_ref_mso, psat_power_ref_lso, psat_drv_bias, psat_pa_bias, max_adjust_up_mso, max_adjust_up_lso, max_adjust_down_mso, max_adjust_down_lso].

config_element.name: unifiClearRadioTrimCache
config_element.description_user: Clears the radio trim cache. The parameter is ignored.
config_element.description_internal: Invalidates all entries in the trim cache.

config_element.name: unifiRxAgcControl
config_element.description_user:
Override the AGC by adjusting the Rx minimum and maximum gains of each stage. Set requests write the values to a static structure in mac/arch/maxwell/hal/halradio_agc.c. The saved values are written to the Jar register WLRF_RADIO_AGC_CONFIG2 and to the Night registers WL_RADIO_AGC_CONFIG2 and WL_RADIO_AGC_CONFIG3. The saved values are also used to configure the AGC whenever halradio_agc_setup() is called. Get requests read the values from the static structure in mac/arch/maxwell/hal/halradio_agc.c. AGC enables are not altered. Fixed gain may be tested by setting the minimums and maximums to the same value.
Version. octet 0 - Version number for this mib. Gain values. Default in brackets. octet 1 - 5G LNA minimum gain (0). octet 2 - 5G LNA maximum gain (4). octet 3 - 2G LNA minimum gain (0). octet 4 - 2G LNA maximum gain (5). octet 5 - Mixer minimum gain (0). octet 6 - Mixer maximum gain (2). octet 7 - ABB minimum gain (0). octet 8 - ABB maximum gain (27). octet 9 - Digital minimum gain (0). octet 10 - Digital maximum gain (7).

config_element.name: unifiTxAntennaConnectionLossFrequency
config_element.description_user: The corresponding set of frequency values for TxAntennaConnectionLossTable

config_element.name: unifiTxAntennaConnectionLoss
config_element.description_user: The set of Antenna Connection Loss value, which is used for TPO/EIRP conversion

config_element.name: unifiTxAntennaMaxGainFrequency
config_element.description_user: The corresponding set of frequency values for TxAntennaMaxGain

config_element.name: unifiTxAntennaMaxGain
config_element.description_user: The set of Antenna Max Gain value, which is used for TPO/EIRP conversion

config_element.name: unifiRxExternalGainFrequency
config_element.description_user: The set of RSSI offset value

config_element.name: unifiRxExternalGain
config_element.description_user: The table giving frequency-dependent RSSI offset value

config_element.name: unifiCurrentTxpowerLevel
config_element.description_user: Maximum air power for the VIF. Values are expressed in 0.25 dBm units.

config_element.name: unifiDebugInstantDelivery
config_element.description_user: Instant delivery control of the debug messages when set to true. Note: will not allow the host to suspend when set to True.

config_element.name: unifiDebugEnable
config_element.description_user: Debug to host state. Debug is either is sent to the host or it isn't.

config_element.name: unifiDebugModuleControl
config_element.description_user:
Debug Module levels for all modules. Module debug level is used to filter debug messages sent to the host. Only 6 levels of debug per module are available: a. -1 No debug created. b. 0 Debug if compiled in. Should not cause Buffer Full in normal testing. c. 1 - 3 Levels to allow sensible setting of the .hcf file while running specific tests or debugging d. 4 Debug will harm normal execution due to excessive levels or processing time required. Only used in emergency debugging. Additional control for FSM transition and FSM signals logging is provided.
Debug module level and 2 boolean flags are encoded within a uint16: Function | Is sending FSM signals | Is sending FSM transitions | Reseved | Module level (signed int) ----------+--------------------------+------------------------------+-----------+---------------------------- Bits | 15 | 14 | 13 - 8 | 7 - 0
Note: 0x00FF disables any debug for a module 0xC004 enables all debug for a module

config_element.name: unifiTxOOBConstraints
config_element.description_user: OOB constraints table. | octects | description | |---------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | 0 | DPD applicability bitmask: 0 = no DPD, 1 = dynamic DPD, 2 = static DPD, 3 = applies to both static and dynamic DPD | | 1-2 | Bitmask indicating which regulatory domains this rule applies to FCC=bit0, ETSI=bit1, JAPAN=bit2 | | 3-4 | Bitmask indicating which band edges this rule applies to RICE_BAND_EDGE_ISM_24G_LOWER = bit 0, RICE_BAND_EDGE_ISM_24G_UPPER = bit 1, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_1_LOWER = bit 2, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_1_UPPER = bit 3, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_2_LOWER = bit 4, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_2_UPPER = bit 5, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_2E_LOWER = bit 6, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_2E_UPPER = bit 7, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_3_LOWER = bit 8, RICE_BAND_EDGE_U_NII_3_UPPER = bit 9 | | 5 | Bitmask indicating which modulation types this rule applies to (LSB/b0=DSSS/CCK, b1= OFDM0 modulation group, b2= OFDM1 modulation group) | | 6 | Bitmask indicating which channel bandwidths this rule applies to (LSB/b0=20MHz, b1=40MHz, b2=80MHz) | | 7 | Minimum distance to nearest band edge in 500 kHz units for which this constraint becomes is applicable. | | 8 | Maximum power (EIRP) for this particular constraint - specified in units of quarter dBm. | | 9-32 | Spectral shaping configuration to be used for this particular constraint. The value is specific to the radio hardware and should only be altered under advice from the IC supplier. | |

config_element.name: unifiRegDomVersion
config_element.description_user: Regulatory domain version encoded into 2 bytes, major version as MSB and minor version as LSB

config_element.name: unifiRegulatoryParameters
config_element.description_user: Regulatory parameters. Each row of the table contains the regulatory rules for one country: octet 0 - first character of alpha2 code for country octet 1 - second character of alpha2 code for country octet 2 - regulatory domain for the country Followed by the rules for the country, numbered 0..n in this description octet 7n+3 - LSB start frequency octet 7n+4 - MSB start frequency octet 7n+5 - LSB end frequency octet 7n+6 - MSB end frequency octet 7n+7 - maximum bandwidth octet 7n+8 - maximum power octet 7n+9 - rule flags

config_element.name: unifiOperatingClassTableIndex
config_element.description_user: Index for unifiOperatingClassTable

config_element.name: unifiOperatingClassParamters
config_element.description_user: Supported Operating Class parameters.

config_element.name: unifiScanParametersTableIndex
config_element.description_user: Index for unifiScanParametersTable. Index is a Scan_Type as defined in FAPI.

config_element.name: unifiScanParameters
config_element.description_user: Scan parameters. Each row of the table contains 2 entries for a scan: first entry when there is 0 registered VIFs, second - when there is 1 or more registered VIFs. Entry has the following structure: octet 0 - Scan priority (uint8_t) octet 1 - Enable Early Channel Exit (uint8_t as bool) octet 2 ~ 3 - Probe Interval in Time Units (uint16_t) octet 4 ~ 5 - Max Active Channel Time in Time Units (uint16_t) octet 6 ~ 7 - Max Passive Channel Time in Time Units (uint16_t) octet 8 ~ 9 - Scan Policy (uint16_t) Size of each entry is 10 octets, row size is 20 octets. A Time Units value specifies a time interval as a multiple of TU (1024 us).

config_element.name: unifiTdlsInP2pActivated
config_element.description_user: Use TDLS in P2P mode.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsActivated
config_element.description_user: Use TDLS mode.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTPThresholdPktSecs
config_element.description_user: Used for the argument "throughput_threshold_pktsecs" of RAME-MLME-ENABLE-PEER-TRAFFIC-REPORTING.request signal defined in SC-505422-DD.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsRssiThreshold
config_element.description_user: Used for the FW initiated TDLS Discovery/Setup procedure. If the RSSI of a received TDLS Discovery Response frame is greater than this value,the TDLS FSM shall initiate the TDLS Setup procedure.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsMaximumRetry
config_element.description_user: Transmission of a TDLS Action frame or a TDLS Discovery Response Public Action frame shall be retried unifiTdlsMaximumRetry times until the frame is transmitted successfully.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTPMonitorSecs
config_element.description_user: The measurement period for recording the number of packets sent to a peer over a TDLS link.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsBasicHtMcsSet
config_element.description_user: The default Basic HT MCS SET used on a TDLS Link. Used to build the HT Operation element in TDLS Setup frames.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsBasicVhtMcsSet
config_element.description_user: Used to build the VHT Operation element in the TDLS Setup Confirm frame

config_element.name: dot11TDLSDiscoveryRequestWindow
config_element.description_user: TDLS shall not transmit the TDLS Discovery Request frame within dot11TDLSDiscoveryRequestWindow DTIM intervals after transmitting TDLS Discovery Request frame.

config_element.name: dot11TDLSResponseTimeout
config_element.description_user: If no TDLS Setup Response frame is received within dot11TDLSResponseTimeout, or if a TDLS Setup Response frame is received with a nonzero status code, the TDLS initiator STA shall terminate the setup procedure and discard the TDLS Setup Response frame.

config_element.name: dot11TDLSChannelSwitchActivated
config_element.description_user: When true, indicates that the STA implementation is capable of supporting TDLS Channel Switching.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsDesignForTestMode
config_element.description_user: Set TDLS design for test mode

config_element.name: unifiTdlsKeyLifeTimeInterval
config_element.description_user: Build the Key Lifetime Interval in the TDLS Setup Request frame.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTeardownFrameTxTimeout
config_element.description_user: Allowed time in milliseconds for a TDLS Teardown frame to be trasmitted over the air

config_element.name: unifiWifiSharingEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enabled Wifi Sharing feature

config_element.name: unifiWiFiSharing5GHzChannel
config_element.description_user: Applicable 5GHz Primary Channels mask. Defined in a uint64 represented by the octet string. First byte of the octet string maps to LSB. Bits 0-13 representing 2.4G channels are always set to 0. Mapping defined in mlme_freq_list[]; i.e. Bit 14 maps to channel 36.

config_element.name: unifiWifiSharingChannelSwitchCount
config_element.description_user: Channel switch announcement count which will be used in the Channel announcement IE when using wifi sharing

config_element.name: unifiChannelAnnouncementCount
config_element.description_user: Channel switch announcement count which will be used in the Channel announcement IE

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApActivated
config_element.description_user: ChanelSwitch: Enable waiting for a slow AP.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApMaxTime
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch delay for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApPollInterval
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch polling interval for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApProcedureTimeoutIncrement
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch procedure timeout increment for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiRATestStoredSA
config_element.description_user: Source address of router assuming that is contained in virtural router advertisement packet is only used for the test purpose, specified in chapter '6.2 Forward Received RA frame to Host' in SC-506393-TE

config_element.name: unifiRATestStoreFrame
config_element.description_user: Virtual router advertisement packet is only used for the test purpose, specified in chapter '6.2 Forward Received RA frame to Host' in SC-506393-TE

config_element.name: dot11TDLSPeerUAPSDBufferSTAActivated
config_element.description_user: Indicate that the STA implementation is capable of supporting TDLS peer U-APSD.

config_element.name: unifiSupportedChannels
config_element.description_user: Supported 20MHz channel centre frequency grouped in sub-bands. For each sub-band: starting channel number, followed by number of channels

config_element.name: unifiDefaultCountry
config_element.description_user: Allows setting of default country code. Hosts sets the default country (index 1). Each VIF maintains current country code and updates it, but never reads. The host can access currently used country code of each VIF, but can't modify it.

config_element.name: unifiDefaultCountryWithoutCH12CH13
config_element.description_user: Update the default country code to ensure CH12 and CH13 are not used.

config_element.name: unifiCountryList
config_element.description_user: Defines the ordered list of countries present in unifiRegulatoryTable. Each country is coded as 2 ASCII characters. If unifiRegulatoryTable is modified, such as a country is either added, deleted or its relative location is modified, has to be updated as well.

config_element.name: unifiStationQosInfo
config_element.description_user: QoS capability for a non-AP Station, and is encoded as per IEEE 802.11 QoS Capability.

config_element.name: unifiListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif power saving mode and receiving DTIMs is enabled. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of the listen interval beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for STA VIF, connected to an AP. For P2P group client intervals, refer to unifiP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2523.

config_element.name: unifiP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif, P2P client power saving mode and receiving DTIMs. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of (listen interval - 1) beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for P2P group client. For STA connected to an AP, refer to unifiListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2518.

config_element.name: unifiListenIntervalMaxTime
config_element.description_user: Maximum number length of time, in Time Units (1TU = 1024us), that can be used as a beacon listen interval. This will limit how many beacons maybe skipped, and affects the DTIM beacon skipping count; DTIM skipping (if enabled) will be such that skipped count = (unifiListenIntervalMaxTime / DTIM_period).

config_element.name: unifiListenInterval
config_element.description_user: Beacon Listen Interval

config_element.name: unifiBeaconsReceivedPercentage
config_element.description_user: Percentage of beacons received, calculated as received / expected. The percentage is scaled to an integer value between 0 (0%) and 1000 (100%).

config_element.name: unifiHtCapabilities
config_element.description_user: HT capabilities of the chip. See SC-503520-SP for further details. NOTE: Greenfield has been disabled due to interoperability issues wuth SGI.

config_element.name: unifiVhtCapabilities
config_element.description_user: VHT capabilities of the chip. see SC-503520-SP.

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseTimeOut
config_element.description_user: How long to wait for a frame (Auth, Assoc, ReAssoc) after Rame replies to a send frame request

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseCfmTxLifetimeTimeOut
config_element.description_user: How long to wait to retry a frame (Auth, Assoc, ReAssoc) after TX Cfm trasnmission_status = TxLifetime.

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseCfmFailureTimeOut
config_element.description_user: How long to wait to retry a frame (Auth, Assoc, ReAssoc) after TX Cfm trasnmission_status != Successful | TxLifetime.

config_element.name: unifiConnectionFailureTimeout
config_element.description_user: How long the complete connection procedure has before the MLME times out and issues a Connect Indication (fail).

config_element.name: unifiConnectingProbeTimeout
config_element.description_user: How long to wait for a ProbeRsp when syncronising before resending a ProbeReq

config_element.name: unifiDisconnectTimeout
config_element.description_user: How long the firmware attempts to perform a disconnect or disconnect all STAs (triggered by MLME_DISCONNECT-REQ or MLME_DISCONNECT-REQ 00:00:00:00:00:00) before responding with MLME-DISCONNECT-IND and aborting the disconnection attempt. This is particulary important when a SoftAP is attempting to disconnect associated stations which might have "silently" left the ESS.

config_element.name: unifiForceActiveDuration
config_element.description_user: How long the firmware temporarily extends PowerSave for STA as a workaround for wonky APs such as D-link.

config_element.name: unifiBaTxEnableTid
config_element.description_user: Configure BA TX on a per-TID basis. Bit mask is two bits per TID (B1 = autosetup, B0 = enable).

config_element.name: unifiBaConfig
config_element.description_user: Block Ack Configuration. It is composed of A-MSDU supported, TX MPDU per A-MPDU, RX Buffer size, TX Buffer size and Block Ack Timeout. see init_mlme_ba() for more detail

config_element.name: unifiMoveBKtoBE
config_element.description_user: Enable or disable workaround to make the Dataplane translate AC_BK data into AC_BE data

config_element.name: unifiSupportedDataRates
config_element.description_user: Defines the supported non-HT data rates. It is encoded as N+1 octets where the first octet is N and the subsequent octets each describe a single supported rate.

config_element.name: unifiDualBandConcurrency
config_element.description_user: Identify whether the chip supports dualband concurrency or not.

config_element.name: unifiApOlbcDuration
config_element.description_user: How long the AP enables reception of BEACON frames to perform Overlapping Legacy BSS Condition(OLBC). If set to 0 then OLBC is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiApOlbcInterval
config_element.description_user: How long between periods of receiving BEACON frames to perform Overlapping Legacy BSS Condition(OLBC). This value MUST exceed the OBLC duration MIB unifiApOlbcDuration. If set to 0 then OLBC is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiMaxClient
config_element.description_user: Restricts the maximum number of associated STAs for SoftAP.

config_element.name: unifiPMFAssociationComebackTimeDelta
config_element.description_user: indicates a delta time for the assocication comeback time element in the SA Query request frame. The association comeback time in the SA Query request frame will be set to TSF + unifiPMFAssociationComebackTimeDelta.

config_element.name: unifiScanAbsenceDuration
config_element.description_user: Duration of the Absence time to use when protecting P2PGO VIFs from scan operations. A value of 0 disables the feature.

config_element.name: unifiScanAbsencePeriod
config_element.description_user: Period of the Absence/Presence times cycles to use when protecting P2PGO VIFs from scan operations.

config_element.name: unifiVhtActivated
config_element.description_user: Enables VHT mode.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundEnable
config_element.description_user: Enables the PLM workaround to do an HT reasociation if the initial VHT association succeeded.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerDHCPDiscoverCount
config_element.description_user: Start the PLM workaround timer after unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerDHCPDiscovercount DHCP discover frames sent by the host.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerDHCPDiscoverTimeout
config_element.description_user: Triggers the PLM workaround after unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerDHCPDiscoverTimeout milliseconds after unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerDHCPDiscovercountDHCP discover frames sent by the host.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundAddresses
config_element.description_user: VHT capabilities of the chip. see SC-503520-SP.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerStaticIPTimeout
config_element.description_user: Triggers the static PLM workaround after unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerStaticIPTimeout milliseconds.

config_element.name: unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerARPCount
config_element.description_user: Triggers the static PLM workaround after unifiPLM689WorkaroundTriggerARPCount ARP requests were sent.

config_element.name: unifiTqamActivated
config_element.description_user: Enables Vendor VHT IE for 256-QAM mode on 2.4GHz.

config_element.name: unifiHtActivated
config_element.description_user: Enables HT mode.

config_element.name: unifiWipsActivated
config_element.description_user: Enables Wips.

config_element.name: unifi24G40MHZChannels
config_element.description_user: Enables 40Mz wide channels in the 2.4G band

config_element.name: unifiTxUsingLdpcEnabled
config_element.description_user: LDPC will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send LDPC coded packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of LDPC coded packets,enable bit 0 of unifiHtCapabilities, and bit 4 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI20Enabled
config_element.description_user: SGI 20MHz will be used to code packets for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 20MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 20MHz packets, enable bit 5 of unifiHtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI40Enabled
config_element.description_user: SGI 40MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 40MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 40MHz packets, enable bit 6 of unifiHtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI80Enabled
config_element.description_user: SGI 80MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 80MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 80MHz packets, enable bit 5 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI160Enabled
config_element.description_user: SGI 160/80+80MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 160/80+80MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 160/80+80MHz packets, enable bit 6 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiMacAddressRandomisation
config_element.description_user: Mac Address Randomisation should be applied for Probe Requests.

config_element.name: unifiSuBeamformerEnabled
config_element.description_user: SU Beamformer will be used, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not use SU Beamformer even if peer supports it. To advertise SU Beamformee capability, enable bit 12 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiMuBeamformerEnabled
config_element.description_user: MU Beamformer will be used, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not use MU Beamformer even if peer supports it. To advertise MU Beamformee capability, enable bit 20 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiMacAddressRandomisationMask
config_element.description_user: FW randomises MAC Address bits that have a corresponding bit set to 0 in the MAC Mask for Probe Requests. This excludes U/L and I/G bits which will be set to Local and Individual respectively.

config_element.name: unifiMacSequenceNumberRandomisationActivated
config_element.description_user: Enabling Sequence Number Randomisation to be applied for Probe Requests when scanning. Note: Randomisation only happens, if mac address gets randomised.

config_element.name: unifiRoamingEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable Roaming functionality

config_element.name: unifiRoamingInP2pActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Roaming in P2P.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: The current RSSI value below which roaming scan shall start

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiScanNoCandidateDeltaTrigger
config_element.description_user: The value, in dBm, by which unifiRoamRssiScanTrigger is lowered when no roaming candidates are found.

config_element.name: unifiRoamDeltaTrigger
config_element.description_user: Hysteresis value, in dBm, for UnifiRoamRssiScanTrigger and unifiRoamCUScanTrigger. i.e.: If the current AP RSSI is greater than UnifiRoamRssiScanTrigger + UnifiRoamRssiDeltaTrigger, soft roaming scan can be terminated.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCachedChannelScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The scan period for cached channels background roaming (microseconds)

config_element.name: UnifiRoamTrackingScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The scan period for tracking not yet suitable candidate(s)(microseconds)

config_element.name: unifiRoamConnectionQualityCheckWaitAfterConnect
config_element.description_user: The amount of time a STA will wait after connection before starting to check the MLME-installed connection quality trigger thresholds

config_element.name: unifiRoamScanBand
config_element.description_user: Indicates whether only intra-band or all-band should be used for roaming scan. 2 - Roaming across band 1 - Roaming within band

config_element.name: unifiRoamFullChannelScanFrequency
config_element.description_user: Every how many cached channel scans run a full channel scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamMode
config_element.description_user: Enable/Disable host resume when roaming. 0: Wake up the host all the time. 1: Only wakeup the host if the AP is not white-listed. 2: Don't wake up the host.

config_element.name: unifiRoamEAPTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout for receiving the first EAP/EAPOL frame from the AP during roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamRSSIBoost
config_element.description_user: The value in dBm of the RSSI boost for each band

config_element.name: unifiRoamCuLocal
config_element.description_user: Channel utilisation for the STA VIF, value 255=100% channel utilisation. - used for roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUScanNoCandidateDeltaTrigger
config_element.description_user: The delta, in percentage points, to apply to unifiRoamCUScanTrigger when no candidate found during first cycle of cached channel soft scan, triggered by channel utilization.

config_element.name: unifiRoamAPSelectDeltaFactor
config_element.description_user: Candidate AP selection delta versus current AP that triggers a roam.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUWeight
config_element.description_user: Weight of CUfactor, in percentage points, in AP selection algorithm.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUFactor
config_element.description_user: Bi dimensional octet string table for allocating CUfactor to CU values. First index is the radio band, and the second will be CU table entry. The tables define the maximum CU value to which the values do apply(MAX CU), an OFFSET and an A value for the equation: CUfactor = OFFSET - A*(CU)/10

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiweight
config_element.description_user: Weight of RSSI factor, in percentage points, in AP selection algorithm.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiFactor
config_element.description_user: Table allocating RSSIfactor to RSSI values range.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCURssiScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: The current channel Averaged RSSI value below which a soft roaming scan shall initially start, providing high channel utilisation (see unifiRoamCUScanTrigger). This is a table indexed by frequency band.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: BSS Load / Channel Utilisation doesn't need to be monitored more than every 10th Beacons. This is a table indexed by frequency band.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBSSLoadMonitoringFrequency
config_element.description_user: How often should the BSS load be monitored? - used for roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamBSSCUTriggerFrequency
config_element.description_user: How long, in received beacons, should the BSS load be high before triggering roaming?

config_element.name: unifiRoamOffloaded4wshkTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time allowed before an attempt to do an offloaded 4 way handshake is considered failed?

config_element.name: unifiRoamBlacklistSize
config_element.description_user: Do not remove! Read by the host! And then passed up to the framework.

config_element.name: unifiNchoActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Network Controlled Hand Over (NCHO)

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanControl
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Indicates which control path shall be evaluated in order to determine which channels should be scanned for NCHO scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoDfsScanMode
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies how DFS channels should be scanned for roaming. For certification and Host use only. 0: DFS roaming scan disabled. 1: DFS roaming scan enabled. Normal mode. i.e. passive scanning on DFS channels (Default) 2: DFS roaming scan enabled with active scanning on channel list supplied with MLME-SET-CACHED-CHANNELS.request

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoFullScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the period at which the full channel scan shall be run. For certification and Host use only.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoCachedScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the period at which the cached channel scan shall be run. For certification and Host use only.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanMaxActiveChannelTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the maximum time spent scanning a channel.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanNProbe
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The number of ProbeRequest frames per channel.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanHomeTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The time, in TU, to spend NOT scanning during a HomeAway scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanHomeAwayTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The time, in TU, to spend scanning during a HomeAway scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiDelta
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the RSSI delta at a potential candidate is deemed eligible.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiTrigger
config_element.description_user: The current channel Averaged RSSI value below which a NCHO scan shall start.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiTriggerHysteresis
config_element.description_user: Hysteresis value that added to unifiRoamNchoRssiTrigger will result in the RSSI value that will stop eventual NCHO scans.

config_element.name: dot11TDLSPeerUAPSDIndicationWindow
config_element.description_user: The minimum time that needs to pass after the most recent TPU SP, before a RAME_TPU_SP indication can be sent to MLME

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxHostRate
config_element.description_user: Fixed TX rate set by Host. Ideally this should be done by the driver. 0 means "host did not specified any rate".

config_element.name: unifiWMMStallEnable
config_element.description_user: For testing: Enable workaround stall WMM traffic if the admitted time has been used up, used for cert testing

config_element.name: unifiRaaSpeculationInterval
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the repeatable amount of time, in ms, that firmware will start to send speculation frames.

config_element.name: unifiRaaSpeculationPeriod
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the max amount of time, in ms, that firmware will use for sending speculation frames

config_element.name: unifiRaaNumbSpeculationFrames
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the max amount of speculation frames that firmware is allowed to send.

config_element.name: unifiRaaMaxSpecTimerMultiplier
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the max number to be multiplied to the speculation timer, which usually is 100 ms.

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxSuccessesCount
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It represents the number of transmitted frames that were acked at a given rate.

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxFailuresCount
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It represents the number of transmitted frames that were NOT acked at a given rate.

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxPer
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It represents the Packet Error Rate for a given rate on the RAA rate stats.

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxMTPer
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It represents the Maximum Tolerable Packet Error Rate for each rate.

config_element.name: unifiRaaResetStats
config_element.description_user: For Rate Adaptation Algorithm. It Resets the stats table used by the RAA.

config_element.name: unifiLaaProtectionConfigOverride
config_element.description_user: Overrides the default Protection configuration. Only valid flag is DPIF_CONFIG_INFO_PROTECTION_TXOP_AMPDU. Default allows protection code to work out the rules based on configuration. If DPIF_CONFIG_INFO_PROTECTION_TXOP_AMPDU is unset then, the first A-MPDU in the TxOp is no longer protected.

config_element.name: unifiFallbackShortFrameRetryDistribution
config_element.description_user: Configure the retry distribution for fallback for short frames octet 0 - Number of retries for starting rate. octet 1 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 2 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 3 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 4 - Number of retries for last rate. If 0 is written to an entry then the retries for that rate will be the short retry limit minus the sum of the retries for each rate above that entry (e.g. 15 - 5). Therefore, this should always be the value for octet 4. Also, when the starting rate has short guard enabled, the number of retries in octet 1 will be used and for the next rate in the fallback table (same MCS value, but with sgi disabled) octet 0 number of retries will be used.

config_element.name: unifiThroughputDebug
config_element.description_user: is used to access throughput related counters that can help diagnose throughput problems. The index of the MIB will access different counters, as described in SC-506328-DD. Setting any index for a VIF to any value, clears all DPLP debug stats for the MAC instance used by the VIF. This is useful mainly for debugging LAA or small scale throughput issues that require short term collection of the statistics.

config_element.name: unifiRadioLpRxRssiThresholdUpper

config_element.name: unifiDPDTrainPacketConfig
config_element.description_user: This MIB allows the dummy packets training bandwidth and rates to be overriden. Tipically the bandwidth would be the same as the channel bandwidth (for example 80 MHz packets for an 80 Mhz channel) and rates MCS1 and MCS5. With this MIB you can set, for example, an 80 MHz channel to be trained using 20 MHz bandwidth (centered or not) with MCS2 and MCS7 packets. The MIB index dictates what channel bandwidth the configuration is for (1 for 20 MHz, 2 for 40 MHz and so on). The format is: - octet 0: train bandwidth (this basically follows the halradio_channel_bw enum). - octet 1: train primary channel position - octet 2-3: OFDM 0 rate - octet 4-5: OFDM 1 rate - octet 6-7: CCK rate (unused) The rates are encoded in host(FAPI) format, see SC-506179, section 4.41.
